Asarco reconsiders Black Cloud shutdown . Asarco Inc said it has reconsidered its recent decision to shut down its Black Cloud mine in Leadville , Colo . , and has decided to resume mine operations early in 1997 . Recall of mine workers will begin early in January with the restart of operations to be phased in during January with resumption of fully employment at the mine by February 1 . Full production is expected to be resumed at the mine by mid - March , Asarco said . In 1995 , the mine produced 15 , 400 short tons of zinc , 5 , 000 tons of lead and 340 , 000 ounces of silver . - - Jim Brumm 212 - 859 - 1710 
